President Muhammadu Buhari may have sent the list of 42 Ministers expected to form his new cabinet to the Senate. The list was tarnsfered to the National Assembly Monday evening, a source told DAILY ASSET. According to the source, 12 ministers from the former cabinet made the list which had a nominee each from the 36 states of the Federation and one each from a geo-political zone making 42 all together. The Senate is likely to read the list on the floor on Tuesday and screen all the Ministers before proceeding on recess from Thursday, DAILY ASSET was told. â€¦Details of nominees later (Daily Asset)